06:14.749 --> 06:15.917
One more, one more.

06:15.958 --> 06:17.627
One more.

06:17.668 --> 06:19.253
I can see why this paradeis so popular.

06:19.253 --> 06:20.296
He's incredible.

06:21.255 --> 06:22.632
Oh!

06:22.673 --> 06:24.050
Oh, that's so nice.

06:26.260 --> 06:27.345
How did you do that?

06:27.387 --> 06:30.014
I have my connections.

06:30.640 --> 06:32.350
Well, how aboutwe all go inside

06:32.391 --> 06:34.435
for some famousLong Family eggnog?

06:34.477 --> 06:36.229
Now, you don'thave to ask me twice.

06:36.270 --> 06:38.106
-Good idea.-Perfect.

06:38.106 --> 06:39.482
Thank you, dear.

06:39.524 --> 06:40.525
You're welcome.

06:40.566 --> 06:42.360
There you go.

06:42.401 --> 06:43.903
And a Ho-ho--

06:52.870 --> 06:53.996
Oh, no!

06:54.038 --> 06:56.415
Tom!

06:56.457 --> 06:57.333
Are you okay?

06:57.375 --> 06:58.501
Where does it hurt?

06:58.543 --> 06:59.752
Just the arm,

06:59.794 --> 07:01.462
but I've got another one.

07:01.504 --> 07:03.840
Okay, well, we shouldprobably get you inside.

07:03.881 --> 07:05.550
Okay, one, two, three,ready?

07:05.591 --> 07:07.051
[yelping in pain]

07:07.093 --> 07:08.010
Oh! Oh...

07:08.052 --> 07:09.095
I'm okay.

07:09.137 --> 07:10.138
-You okay?-I'm okay.

07:10.138 --> 07:11.097
All right.

07:13.516 --> 07:16.144
What are we going to doabout the Parade, Tom?

07:16.185 --> 07:17.812
You can't be Santa.

07:17.854 --> 07:19.647
Of courseI can still be Santa.

07:19.647 --> 07:21.274
The parade is a week away.

07:21.315 --> 07:22.400
I'll be right as rain-dear.

07:22.442 --> 07:23.985
You see whatI did there?

07:24.026 --> 07:24.819
Sweetheart,

07:25.027 --> 07:27.196
you can't do your jobwith a big cast.

07:27.238 --> 07:28.322
But the 50thanniversary parade

07:28.364 --> 07:29.657
is in a week,

07:29.699 --> 07:31.951
and the whole townis counting on me.

07:31.993 --> 07:33.411
[wincing]

07:33.452 --> 07:36.080
Tom, don't worryabout me, okay?

07:36.122 --> 07:37.915
I'm so sorry, Grace.

07:40.334 --> 07:41.919
Call Georgeat the Santa School,

07:41.961 --> 07:44.172
ask him if any of our formerstudents are available.

07:44.213 --> 07:46.424
Everyone's booked.

07:46.466 --> 07:48.342
You've trained themso well,

07:48.342 --> 07:50.052
they're in high demand.

07:50.094 --> 07:51.512
Normally, I would be happyto hear that,

07:51.554 --> 07:52.638
but not today.

07:52.680 --> 07:53.639
Careful.

07:53.681 --> 07:54.932
Tom, you just--

07:54.974 --> 07:56.684
you stay hereand rest, okay?

07:56.726 --> 07:57.894
-Okay.-All right.

07:57.935 --> 07:59.562
The important thingis you rest right now.

07:59.604 --> 08:02.148
We'll find someone.

08:07.195 --> 08:09.864
Ho-ho-ho!Ho-ho-ho...

08:09.864 --> 08:11.699
[Grace]: Like I saidbefore, everyone,

08:11.699 --> 08:13.492
find the jolly!

08:13.534 --> 08:14.494
Okay, Jim,

08:14.535 --> 08:15.953
pretend I'm next up in line.

08:15.995 --> 08:17.205
Okay.

08:17.205 --> 08:19.207
So...[clearing throat]

08:19.248 --> 08:21.209
What would you like Santato bring you for Christmas?

08:21.250 --> 08:22.210
Ho-ho-ho!

08:22.251 --> 08:23.502
A pony.

08:24.462 --> 08:25.838
What's the square footageof your property?

08:25.880 --> 08:27.715
Do you havethe necessary permits?

08:27.757 --> 08:30.218
Have you even notifiedthe planning commission?

08:30.218 --> 08:31.302
You know what, Jim,

08:31.636 --> 08:33.513
I think you should probablyjust stick with city council.

08:33.554 --> 08:34.514
Yeah.

08:34.554 --> 08:35.514
Okay.

08:35.556 --> 08:36.849
Next?

08:37.558 --> 08:39.101
Please have a seat.

08:39.769 --> 08:43.313
All right, um, let's see.

08:43.356 --> 08:44.482
Do you know,

08:44.524 --> 08:45.900
I'm thinkinga little more beard.

08:47.235 --> 08:49.445
Yeah, not beardy enough.

08:49.487 --> 08:51.072
Beardy..?

08:51.113 --> 08:52.114
Next!

08:52.156 --> 08:53.491
Thank you, though.

08:57.745 --> 09:00.498
Aren't youMayor Harvey's son, Clint?

09:00.539 --> 09:01.624
Yup.

09:01.749 --> 09:04.418
So, I mean, this is just likea formality, right?

09:05.586 --> 09:08.089
Sorry, losers.[chuckles]

09:08.089 --> 09:09.257
That's lunch.

09:10.007 --> 09:12.510
[marching band plays"Jingle Bells"]

09:12.552 --> 09:15.221
[♪♪]

09:22.728 --> 09:23.854
All right,you guys sound great.

09:23.896 --> 09:25.273
You're gonna soundamazing for the parade.

09:25.314 --> 09:27.066
But afterthose auditions,

09:27.108 --> 09:28.734
we stilldon't have a Santa.

09:28.776 --> 09:30.403
How bad can it be?

09:32.071 --> 09:34.865
[Grace]: Aren't you Mayor Harvey's son, Clint?

09:34.907 --> 09:38.452
Yup. So, I mean, like, this is just a formality, right?

09:38.452 --> 09:39.954
