13:25.846 --> 13:28.098
[shop bell jingles]

13:45.282 --> 13:46.033
Sorry,

13:46.033 --> 13:47.826
I know I'm hovering,but, uh,

13:47.868 --> 13:49.703
you're almost done, right?

13:49.703 --> 13:50.663
Would it be okay

13:50.704 --> 13:51.914
if I take this tablewhen you leave?

13:51.956 --> 13:53.165
Oh, you know, actually--

13:53.207 --> 13:54.208
It's no rush.Take your time.

13:54.375 --> 13:56.043
It's just kind ofmy "go-to" writing table.

13:56.043 --> 13:58.671
Oh, you're a writer?

13:58.712 --> 14:00.339
What do you write?

14:00.381 --> 14:02.967
Just a...I'm working on a novel.

14:03.008 --> 14:04.218
Hmm.

14:04.260 --> 14:05.302
Well, I'm sorryabout your table,

14:05.344 --> 14:07.179
but I'm not leavingfor a while.

14:08.013 --> 14:10.724
Got a blind date?

14:11.725 --> 14:13.018
I'm looking for Santa Claus.

14:13.060 --> 14:14.770
Isn't hea little old for you?

14:14.812 --> 14:15.771
Okay.

14:15.813 --> 14:17.898
How about Ben White?

14:17.898 --> 14:19.567
Do you know him?

14:19.567 --> 14:21.402
Ben who? N-no.

14:21.443 --> 14:22.403
Mm-mm. Nope.

14:22.444 --> 14:23.487
Here you go, Ben.

14:25.573 --> 14:26.907
Maybe it's that guy.

14:29.743 --> 14:31.495
Could be that guy.

14:33.497 --> 14:34.999
So, to be clear,

14:35.040 --> 14:36.917
you're not Ben White

14:36.959 --> 14:38.502
that went toGreen River High?

14:38.544 --> 14:39.712
No. Not him.

14:39.753 --> 14:40.921
[barista]: Here you go, Ben.

14:42.673 --> 14:43.632
Ben!

14:43.674 --> 14:44.842
Oh. [chuckles]

14:45.759 --> 14:47.469
Sorry, one sec.

14:48.596 --> 14:50.598
Thank you.

14:50.639 --> 14:51.599
Okay, fine.

14:51.599 --> 14:53.058
I'm Grace Long.

14:53.100 --> 14:55.894
I... gathered as much.

14:57.688 --> 14:58.731
Oh, hey.All right.

14:59.940 --> 15:01.650
That was awfully nice of you.

15:01.692 --> 15:03.235
He's a good guy.

15:03.277 --> 15:05.279
He's just down on his luck.

15:07.531 --> 15:08.490
Can I sit?

15:08.532 --> 15:09.491
Yeah, please.

15:09.533 --> 15:13.162
So, I'm sorry, um...

15:13.203 --> 15:14.288
I really hope you didn't comeall the way up here

15:14.330 --> 15:15.331
to try and talk me into this.

15:15.372 --> 15:19.043
Look, Ben, I don't thinkyou understand

15:19.084 --> 15:20.586
what's at stakehere, okay?

15:20.628 --> 15:22.880
This is the 50thanniversary of the parade.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.256
"Good Day, USA" isgoing to be there.

15:24.298 --> 15:27.009
The entire townis counting on the publicity

15:27.051 --> 15:28.469
to bring in new tourism,

15:28.469 --> 15:31.013
and we can't do thatwithout a decent Santa.

15:31.055 --> 15:32.598
I get it, but I'm sorry,

15:32.640 --> 15:34.350
as much as I'd love to help,I'm working on this novel,

15:34.391 --> 15:36.769
and I just can't affordto take any time off.

15:36.810 --> 15:37.937
I could pay you.

15:37.978 --> 15:38.979
No, it's notabout the money.

15:39.021 --> 15:40.105
I just...

15:40.147 --> 15:43.817
being Santa isn't my thing.

15:43.859 --> 15:45.986
Well, I mean, is thereanything I could say

15:46.028 --> 15:47.237
to make you change your mind?

15:47.279 --> 15:49.156
No. I'm sorry.

15:49.156 --> 15:50.324
Look, it's okay.

15:50.449 --> 15:51.450
I'm just going to go aheadand grab another table.

15:51.659 --> 15:53.035
I've to get some work doneon my novel

15:53.077 --> 15:54.787
before someonecalls for a ride.

15:56.038 --> 15:58.082
Calls for a ride?

15:58.123 --> 16:00.125
Yeah, I'ma rideshare driver.

16:00.167 --> 16:01.085
Gotta paythe bills, right?

16:01.126 --> 16:04.171
Anyway, thank youfor your inquiry.

16:04.213 --> 16:06.048
I hope you havea safe trip back.

16:06.090 --> 16:07.508
It's good to see you.

16:07.508 --> 16:08.967
Take care.

16:13.180 --> 16:14.556
You're fake-typing.

16:15.724 --> 16:16.684
No, I'm not.

16:16.725 --> 16:17.768
Really?

16:18.811 --> 16:20.312
So the titleof your novel is...

16:21.313 --> 16:23.565
"Slijrvidsin?"

16:24.566 --> 16:25.609
Yes.

16:25.651 --> 16:27.194
Yes, it is.

16:27.194 --> 16:28.779
It's a coming-of-age pieceset in Sweden.

16:28.821 --> 16:29.822
So...

16:29.863 --> 16:31.615
Now if you'll excuse me.

16:32.491 --> 16:34.785
Okay.

16:56.890 --> 16:58.350
[sighs]

16:59.226 --> 17:01.437
[phone alert chimes]

17:15.659 --> 17:16.910
Hey.

17:16.952 --> 17:18.369
Hi.

17:19.246 --> 17:20.622
Looking for someone?

17:20.664 --> 17:23.834
I just got a messagefor a ride to the train station.

17:23.876 --> 17:25.002
Oh.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.295
Wow, what a coincidence.

17:26.336 --> 17:27.880
I just requested someone.

17:27.921 --> 17:29.923
I mean,what are the odds

17:29.923 --> 17:31.633
that you'd bethe closest Uber driver?

17:31.675 --> 17:33.427
Well, since you're five feetfrom my car,

17:33.427 --> 17:34.887
I'd say about 100%.

17:36.138 --> 17:38.057
That's your car?

17:38.098 --> 17:39.099
That one, yeah.

17:39.099 --> 17:40.726
Perfect.

17:49.109 --> 17:50.778
Should I find someone else?

17:52.279 --> 17:53.864
[sighing] No.[beeps locks open]

17:53.906 --> 17:54.907
That's fine.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.088
[starts engine]

18:24.812 --> 18:25.896
So which station?

18:25.938 --> 18:27.105
Back Bay?

18:29.233 --> 18:31.026
Actually, there's beena change of plans.

18:34.655 --> 18:35.823
[computer voice] Recalculating...

18:35.823 --> 18:36.990
New destination,

18:36.990 --> 18:38.158
Green River, Connecticut.

18:38.158 --> 18:39.409
[brakes screech]

18:41.370 --> 18:42.830
I am not driving youto Connecticut.

18:42.830 --> 18:44.123
Out of the car.

18:44.998 --> 18:46.667
Are you really going to kicka poor, defenseless woman

18:46.708 --> 18:48.085
out of your carin a bad neighborhood?

18:48.126 --> 18:49.503
We're in Beacon Hill!

18:49.545 --> 18:51.171
The only crime around here

18:51.213 --> 18:52.422
is someone parkingwithout a permit.

18:52.464 --> 18:54.049
I'm gonna give youa bad rating.

18:54.091 --> 18:55.300
I'll give youa bad rating.

18:55.342 --> 18:56.260
Ben...

18:56.301 --> 18:58.345
your dad broke his armin two places.

18:58.387 --> 18:59.346
He's in a lot of pain.

18:59.388 --> 19:01.557
I'm sure he'd loveto see you.

19:01.598 --> 19:04.226
And your mom misses you, too.

19:04.268 --> 19:06.520
And with your dadout of commission,

19:06.520 --> 19:09.106
I'm sure she could use the help.

19:09.147 --> 19:10.524
I do need a new laptop.

19:10.566 --> 19:12.442
See? There you go.Win-win.

19:12.484 --> 19:14.862
You're giving upway too easily.

19:14.862 --> 19:17.030
Well, to be honest,

19:17.072 --> 19:18.448
my hopes weren't upvery high anyway.

19:33.714 --> 19:35.591
[turns on music,easy-listening jazz]

19:37.926 --> 19:38.886
Light jazz, huh?

19:40.345 --> 19:41.430
Yeah.

19:41.555 --> 19:43.182
It helps calm me when I havedifficult passengers.

19:45.726 --> 19:48.020
[switches radio stationto Christmas music]

19:48.061 --> 19:49.479
♪ Four calling birds

19:49.521 --> 19:50.898
♪ Three French hens

19:50.898 --> 19:52.065
♪ Two turtle doves

19:52.065 --> 19:54.902
♪ And a partridgein a pear tree! ♪

19:56.486 --> 19:57.738
[switches radio stationback to jazz station]

19:57.738 --> 19:59.364
What, you don't likeChristmas music?

19:59.406 --> 20:01.283
I have a problem withpeople thinking it's okay

20:01.325 --> 20:04.661
just to give someone23 birds.

20:05.370 --> 20:07.205
Okay, that'sactually a good point.

20:10.083 --> 20:11.251
[switches radio station]

20:11.293 --> 20:13.253
[turns off radio]

20:15.088 --> 20:16.882
[rapid clicking on and off]

20:18.342 --> 20:19.718
[turns radio off]

20:56.129 --> 20:57.923
[laughing]

20:58.882 --> 21:00.092
What's so funny?

21:00.133 --> 21:01.468
Nothing.

21:01.510 --> 21:03.136
Here's your coffee.

21:03.136 --> 21:04.763
Thanks.

21:05.514 --> 21:07.140
[car engine starts]

21:17.484 --> 21:19.319
Who are you texting?

21:19.319 --> 21:21.571
None of your business.

21:21.613 --> 21:23.115
My dad, right?

21:24.074 --> 21:24.992
No.

21:25.033 --> 21:26.159
It's my boyfriend.

21:26.159 --> 21:27.744
You don't have a boyfriend.

21:27.786 --> 21:29.496
And how exactlydo you know that?

21:29.538 --> 21:31.957
'Cause he would havedriven you to Boston.

21:32.833 --> 21:33.500
Okay.

21:33.542 --> 21:35.002
Okay, it's your dad.

21:35.043 --> 21:38.755
I'm surprised he figured outhow to text anyway.

21:38.797 --> 21:40.590
Well, he's not quite there yet.

21:40.632 --> 21:42.801
He still signs them "Love, Tom."

21:46.013 --> 21:47.848
Oh, look at that.

21:47.848 --> 21:49.016
You have teeth.

21:49.057 --> 21:50.267
Who knew?

21:50.308 --> 21:51.351
Okay, see?

21:51.435 --> 21:53.103
So why would you even want meas Santa anyway?

21:53.145 --> 21:55.314
I'm obviouslynot jolly enough.

21:56.189 --> 21:57.441
Yeah, why is that?

21:57.482 --> 21:59.317
I'm just not a fanof the holidays in general.

21:59.359 --> 22:01.153
It's too many expectations.

22:01.194 --> 22:02.154
Inevitable disappointment.

22:02.195 --> 22:04.823
It's too many expectations.

22:06.366 --> 22:07.409
My grandparents started it,

22:07.451 --> 22:08.493
and my parents took over,

22:08.535 --> 22:10.454
and now me.

22:10.495 --> 22:12.706
So, I celebrate Christmasevery single day.

22:13.498 --> 22:15.125
Really?

22:15.167 --> 22:16.668
Yeah, what's wrong with that?

22:16.710 --> 22:18.837
Don't you want moreout of life?

22:20.922 --> 22:23.759
I'm perfectly happywith my life choices.

22:23.800 --> 22:26.345
But I appreciateyour concern.

22:32.351 --> 22:35.645
Well, here we are,back in Green River.

22:35.687 --> 22:36.938
Home sweet home.

22:36.980 --> 22:39.441
The parade route looks amazing,don't you think?

22:39.483 --> 22:41.485
Ah, you saidyou wouldn't mention that.

22:41.526 --> 22:44.029
I said I wouldn'tmention Santa.

22:44.071 --> 22:46.198
Look, I'm going to go aheadand drop you off here,

22:46.239 --> 22:47.074
and you can pay.

22:48.533 --> 22:50.035
Oh, you know what,that's perfect,

22:50.077 --> 22:51.328
because I've gotto stop by the Santa school.

22:52.204 --> 22:53.080
Why?

22:53.330 --> 22:55.207
Well, your dad asked meto pick up a box for him.

22:55.248 --> 22:56.708
Are you going to come in?

22:57.834 --> 22:58.710
Uh...

22:58.752 --> 22:59.711
No, that's all right,

22:59.753 --> 23:00.962
I'll just,I'll wait in the car.

23:04.883 --> 23:06.301
Hello?

23:06.343 --> 23:08.720
George?

23:09.513 --> 23:10.388
Is anybody here?

23:10.430 --> 23:11.723
It's Grace.

23:35.163 --> 23:37.124
What is she doing in there?

23:47.592 --> 23:49.386
[train whistle toots]

23:49.428 --> 23:52.848
[♪♪]

24:23.128 --> 24:24.129
Okay...

24:26.381 --> 24:27.799
Ooh, whoops.

24:39.227 --> 24:41.730
Where did youget that?

24:41.771 --> 24:44.691
Oh, it justfell out of the box

24:44.691 --> 24:46.026
with all your dad's stuff.

24:46.067 --> 24:47.027
What is it?

24:47.027 --> 24:50.238
It's basicallya "How-To" manual

24:50.280 --> 24:51.364
for being Santa Claus,

24:51.615 --> 24:53.909
and technically, non-Santasaren't allowed to read it.

24:53.950 --> 24:56.328
Then maybe you shouldput it down, too.

24:58.163 --> 24:59.164
Right.

25:01.666 --> 25:04.377
So, you've gotmy dad's stuff.

25:04.419 --> 25:06.213
Let's go.

25:06.254 --> 25:07.214
Bennie!

25:07.255 --> 25:08.715
You're here!

25:08.757 --> 25:12.219
It's so good to see you.

25:12.260 --> 25:13.053
Hi, George.

25:13.094 --> 25:13.970
You too.

25:14.054 --> 25:16.056
I'm just here to seehow dad's doing.

25:17.307 --> 25:18.517
So I'll get you to your house.

25:18.558 --> 25:19.851
Does my dad know I'm coming?

25:19.893 --> 25:21.645
Uh, yeah, he's at the gazebowith the mayor

25:21.686 --> 25:23.104
getting ready for the ChristmasCandlelight stroll.

25:24.022 --> 25:26.233
I thought you saidhe was in a lot of pain

25:26.233 --> 25:27.234
and needed my help--

25:27.234 --> 25:28.235
[cell phone rings]

25:28.485 --> 25:32.239
Excuse me, it's... a callfrom one of our Santas

25:32.239 --> 25:33.406
in the field.

25:33.448 --> 25:35.367
George here.

25:36.910 --> 25:39.371
"Merry Christmas" in Gaelic?

25:39.412 --> 25:40.372
You've got me stumped.

25:40.413 --> 25:42.207
Hang on.

25:42.249 --> 25:43.875
"Null-eg hunna ghwitch."

25:45.627 --> 25:47.045
[George]: Any chanceyou heard that?

25:47.087 --> 25:48.255
Great.

25:50.465 --> 25:53.385
You still got it, kiddo.

25:55.262 --> 25:56.221
Don't get excited.

25:56.388 --> 25:58.306
I just rememberedfrom one of my classes.

25:58.348 --> 26:01.101
I didn't realize you hadto learn so many languages.

26:01.142 --> 26:04.437
The real Santa can speakto any child in the world,

26:04.479 --> 26:06.439
so our Helper Santas dowhatever it takes

26:06.439 --> 26:07.357
to be like him.

26:07.399 --> 26:09.317
It's a year-roundcommitment,

26:09.359 --> 26:11.194
and a lifetime of joy.

26:12.946 --> 26:16.199
Your dad just wantedto pass that joy on to you.

26:17.784 --> 26:19.619
I had different plans.

26:19.619 --> 26:21.621
I know you did, Ben.

26:30.130 --> 26:32.090
So your dad just wantedto pass on his legacy?

26:34.634 --> 26:37.596
I wanted the freedomto choose, Grace.

26:37.637 --> 26:39.306
Everyone deserves to livetheir own lives,

26:39.347 --> 26:41.516
not someone else's.

26:42.601 --> 26:43.852
Almost forgot,

26:43.893 --> 26:45.979
Tom wanted this, too.

26:45.979 --> 26:47.772
It's a Santa suit.

26:47.814 --> 26:49.524
Oh. Okay.

26:50.483 --> 26:51.443
Thanks, George.

27:26.728 --> 27:29.898
[♪♪]

27:29.939 --> 27:32.692
Ben, there you are!

27:32.734 --> 27:34.027
Hey, Mom.

27:34.069 --> 27:35.612
I'm so happyyou're here!

27:35.653 --> 27:37.364
It's goodto see you.

27:37.405 --> 27:38.490
Where's Dad?

27:38.531 --> 27:39.491
He's in here.

27:39.532 --> 27:41.826
This one is for you...

27:41.868 --> 27:45.372
And this oneis for you.

27:45.372 --> 27:47.207
Merry Christmas.

27:51.461 --> 27:52.379
Ben...

27:52.420 --> 27:54.214
You're here.

27:54.255 --> 27:55.548
Hey, Dad.

27:55.590 --> 27:56.549
Look at you.

27:56.549 --> 27:57.550
You doing okay?

27:57.592 --> 27:58.551
Don't worry about me.

27:58.551 --> 28:00.387
Now that you're here,I'm great.

28:03.181 --> 28:06.518
I'm so happy you decidedto fill in for me as Santa.

28:09.020 --> 28:11.022
I never said that.

28:11.815 --> 28:13.566
Did you tell them I said yes?

28:13.608 --> 28:14.567
Oh...

28:14.609 --> 28:15.693
She didn't say a thing.

28:15.735 --> 28:17.112
We just assumed,

28:17.153 --> 28:18.613
because you cameall this way.

28:18.655 --> 28:21.241
I came becauseI thought you needed me.

28:21.241 --> 28:22.325
We do need you.

28:22.367 --> 28:23.368
To be Santa.

28:24.577 --> 28:26.913
Dad, we have talked about this

28:26.955 --> 28:28.248
so many times.

28:28.248 --> 28:30.542
Okay, my entire childhoodwas Santa 24/7

28:30.583 --> 28:31.710
until I left for college.

28:31.751 --> 28:32.711
All you talked about

28:32.794 --> 28:34.421
was how one dayI would take your place.

28:34.462 --> 28:37.924
Did you realize how muchpressure that put me under?

28:37.924 --> 28:39.551
Ben, it's okay--

28:39.592 --> 28:40.552
No, it's not okay.

28:40.844 --> 28:42.679
You're happy followingin your family's footsteps.

28:42.721 --> 28:44.556
You don't knowwhat it feels like

28:44.597 --> 28:46.224
to want something different.

28:47.183 --> 28:49.185
I told you,I'm happy with what I do.

28:50.854 --> 28:51.730
Okay.

28:52.772 --> 28:54.315
Mom, I'll see youat the house.

28:54.357 --> 28:56.609
Aren't you going to stayfor the stroll?

28:56.609 --> 28:58.445
I mean, we have all the candles.

28:58.445 --> 29:00.321
No, I'm good.

29:03.783 --> 29:05.201
Maybe I can talk himinto it tonight

29:05.243 --> 29:07.829
before he goes back to Boston.

29:07.871 --> 29:09.789
You can try, but...

29:09.831 --> 29:13.126
he's obviouslyalready made up his mind.

29:13.168 --> 29:15.920
[Caroline]: So that's it,he's leaving?

29:15.962 --> 29:17.756
Apparently so.

29:17.797 --> 29:18.757
Too bad.

29:18.798 --> 29:20.717
He was cute.

29:20.759 --> 29:22.760
I didn't bring himhere to date him.

29:22.802 --> 29:25.555
It's called multi-tasking.

29:25.597 --> 29:27.182
Do you thinkabout anything

29:27.223 --> 29:29.225
besides getting meinto a relationship?

29:29.267 --> 29:30.143
Sure.

29:30.185 --> 29:32.687
I think aboutgetting myself into one.

29:32.729 --> 29:33.771
Ah.

29:35.482 --> 29:37.442
Look, it's Ben.

29:39.694 --> 29:40.904
He's still here.

29:40.945 --> 29:42.113
Go talk to him.

29:42.155 --> 29:45.116
Maybe steal his car keysso he's stuck here.

29:45.158 --> 29:47.619
It will just bea waste of time.

29:47.660 --> 29:49.329
Do you haveother plans?

29:52.165 --> 29:53.625
[shop bell jingles]

29:58.963 --> 30:00.048
So...

30:00.089 --> 30:04.636
How's, uh..."Slrfidijrdr" coming?

30:04.677 --> 30:05.637
That's funny.

30:06.888 --> 30:07.847
You mindif I sit down?

30:07.889 --> 30:08.932
Only if you don't--

30:08.973 --> 30:11.017
Ah, I know, I know.I won't--

30:11.059 --> 30:12.644
Not even.. a little bit.

30:12.685 --> 30:13.728
Not at all.

30:13.770 --> 30:14.813
Thank you.

30:16.564 --> 30:18.066
Oh, no thanks.

30:18.107 --> 30:19.150
Oh, come on,it's tradition.

30:19.192 --> 30:20.527
Every store doescookie decorating

30:20.527 --> 30:21.361
during the Stroll.

30:21.528 --> 30:23.154
Pretty sureit's meant for kids.

30:23.863 --> 30:25.156
Just becauseyou're not gonna be Santa

30:25.198 --> 30:27.200
doesn't mean you can't enjoyChristmas a little.

30:27.242 --> 30:28.660
Come on.

30:28.701 --> 30:29.786
Just one cookie.

30:29.827 --> 30:32.205
Okay, but only so I havesomething to eat

30:32.205 --> 30:33.373
on the drive home.

30:33.414 --> 30:34.582
Whatever it takes.

30:53.768 --> 30:54.769
That's great.

31:01.234 --> 31:03.361
Yeah, we'llthrow in a scarf...

31:06.072 --> 31:07.615
That's incredible.

31:07.657 --> 31:08.700
It looks like an oil painting.

31:12.579 --> 31:13.454
My parents,

31:13.580 --> 31:14.747
they did show meone of your paintings

31:14.747 --> 31:16.583
in their house.

31:16.624 --> 31:18.209
You're good.

31:18.960 --> 31:20.628
Painting's just a hobby.

31:20.670 --> 31:22.255
After my parents died,

31:22.255 --> 31:24.757
it sort of fell on meto take over their legacy.

31:24.757 --> 31:25.842
So...

31:25.884 --> 31:26.968
I stepped up.

31:27.010 --> 31:29.596
You know, I didn't run,I did the right thing.

31:29.637 --> 31:31.514
And I'm proud of what I did.

31:33.308 --> 31:34.767
I didn't run either, Grace.

31:34.767 --> 31:36.477
I just walked downa different path.

31:36.519 --> 31:38.396
Are you sureyou chose the right one?

31:39.814 --> 31:41.983
I thought I did.

31:42.025 --> 31:45.570
I just, I spendhalf my time wondering

31:45.612 --> 31:47.780
if my ideas are terrible,

31:47.822 --> 31:48.906
cliché,

31:48.948 --> 31:50.491
or a combination of both.

31:52.076 --> 31:53.369
So, what's your novel about?

31:53.411 --> 31:55.622
It's kind of like"The Outsiders",

31:55.663 --> 31:57.707
but with zombies.

31:57.749 --> 31:59.500
I can't quitefigure out the tone.

31:59.542 --> 32:01.044
Well, isn't it just,

32:01.085 --> 32:02.629
[moaning, zombie-like].."Uughh....

32:02.670 --> 32:04.005
You see?

32:04.047 --> 32:05.048
That's the problem,I was missing that.

32:05.089 --> 32:06.257
I've been doingmore of a--

32:06.299 --> 32:07.634
[roaring, zombie-like]

32:07.634 --> 32:08.301
[laughing]

32:08.509 --> 32:09.510
That's a good zombie, actually.

32:09.552 --> 32:10.303
Thank you.

32:10.428 --> 32:11.554
I think--I think you found it.

32:11.596 --> 32:14.140
Come on, you two,it's a Candlelight Stroll,

32:14.182 --> 32:16.392
not a Candlelight Sit.

32:16.434 --> 32:18.102
The tree lightingis up the street.

32:18.144 --> 32:19.020
Come join us.

32:19.062 --> 32:21.731
A little Christmaswon't kill you, son.

32:21.773 --> 32:23.650
I just told him the same thing!

32:23.691 --> 32:24.567
Great minds.

32:24.609 --> 32:26.903
Mm-hmm.

32:26.944 --> 32:29.155
Merry Christmas, everyone.

32:29.155 --> 32:31.282
What a beautiful evening.

32:31.324 --> 32:33.868
We have lit up the streets,

32:33.910 --> 32:35.787
and now it's timeto light up the tree!

32:35.828 --> 32:37.789
[crowd cheering]

32:38.831 --> 32:40.541
Grace Long, come on up here.

32:41.834 --> 32:42.669
Ladies and gentlemen,

32:42.835 --> 32:45.546
give Gracea huge round of applause.

32:45.588 --> 32:46.673
[crowd cheering]

32:46.714 --> 32:47.590
[Grace]: Thank you.

32:47.799 --> 32:48.758
[quietly] Would you liketo do the honors?

32:49.175 --> 32:51.010
I mean, you deserve itfor getting Tom's son here.

32:51.010 --> 32:52.470
Oh, well,

32:52.512 --> 32:54.138
I didn't,'cause he's not doing it.

32:54.180 --> 32:55.556
[chuckles] Oh...What?

32:55.598 --> 32:56.933
When were you goingto tell me this?

32:56.974 --> 32:58.935
I was goingto tell you tomorrow.

32:58.977 --> 32:59.978
So, who's doing it?

33:00.019 --> 33:01.980
I'm still looking.

33:02.021 --> 33:03.690
Well, my Clint could do it.

33:03.690 --> 33:04.691
He's available.

33:06.859 --> 33:07.860
I mean, you know that.

33:07.860 --> 33:08.861
What are you saying,

33:08.861 --> 33:10.321
Clint's not capableof doing this?

33:10.363 --> 33:13.074
No. No, no,not at all.

33:13.116 --> 33:14.325
Okay, if I can't finda professional,

33:14.367 --> 33:16.119
then Clint's in the suit.

33:16.160 --> 33:18.496
But he has to havea crash course with Tom.

33:18.538 --> 33:19.288
Okay.

33:19.330 --> 33:20.540
He's wonderful!

33:20.540 --> 33:21.416
Yeah. Great. Yeah.

33:21.457 --> 33:22.542
He's just goingto be amazing.

33:22.542 --> 33:23.710
He's got such a waywith people.

33:23.710 --> 33:25.002
Okay.

33:25.044 --> 33:27.046
Okay, great, uh...

33:27.046 --> 33:28.131
All right, everyone.

33:28.172 --> 33:29.465
Ready? Here we go!

33:29.507 --> 33:31.509
[all counting together]Five! Four!

33:31.551 --> 33:33.177
Three! Two!

33:33.219 --> 33:34.721
One!

33:34.762 --> 33:36.597
[cheering]

33:37.390 --> 33:38.558
[groans of disappointment]

33:38.558 --> 33:39.726
Oh.

33:44.397 --> 33:46.858
[Grace]: It's all right,we'll fix it...

33:51.195 --> 33:52.697
Okay, let me try that.

33:53.656 --> 33:56.367
[crowd cheering]

34:00.038 --> 34:01.706
Merry Christmas, everyone.

34:05.042 --> 34:06.252
[mutters] Well, at leastI taught him something.

34:06.294 --> 34:07.962
Tom, leave him be.

34:08.004 --> 34:09.213
I was secretly hopingthat maybe--

34:09.255 --> 34:10.214
I know.

34:10.255 --> 34:12.925
Well, it's getting late,

34:12.925 --> 34:15.011
so we'll be headingback to the house.

34:15.052 --> 34:16.888
What? It's 5:30.

34:17.929 --> 34:19.056
We're old.

34:19.098 --> 34:20.183
I'd like to stay.

34:20.224 --> 34:21.934
--But, uh--

34:21.934 --> 34:23.936
[yawning]--I'm so tired!

34:23.978 --> 34:26.856
Because I'm, uh, old,

34:26.898 --> 34:27.899
and, um...

34:27.940 --> 34:29.025
See you in the morning?

34:29.067 --> 34:29.984
Okay.

34:30.025 --> 34:31.402
And you're stayingat the house, right?

34:31.444 --> 34:34.030
Yeah, but I'm going to beleaving at dawn.

34:34.072 --> 34:35.072
You're notgoing to stay

34:35.114 --> 34:36.199
for Christmas?

34:36.239 --> 34:37.408
Mom, I'm sorry,

34:37.449 --> 34:38.951
Christmas is the busiesttime of year in Boston.

34:38.993 --> 34:40.453
A lot of peopleneed rides.

34:40.453 --> 34:42.163
I'll come back soon.I promise.

34:42.205 --> 34:44.165
Keep that arm elevated, Dad.

34:44.206 --> 34:46.042
I'll see youat the house later, okay?

34:47.418 --> 34:48.878
-Goodnight.-Goodnight.

34:48.920 --> 34:49.920
Good night.

34:50.922 --> 34:52.672
I guess we'llreturn these.

34:52.715 --> 34:54.382
So you're reallyleaving in the morning?

34:54.425 --> 34:55.927
If I leave early enough,

34:55.967 --> 34:57.053
I can beat the traffic.

34:57.094 --> 34:59.013
Okay, well then,I'll go with you.

34:59.055 --> 34:59.972
Why?

35:00.014 --> 35:01.641
Because my caris kinda still there.

35:01.682 --> 35:02.850
What?

35:02.892 --> 35:04.185
You told me you took the train.

35:04.227 --> 35:07.313
Oh, yeah, well, I totally liedto save the parade.

35:07.313 --> 35:08.981
But since you'regoing back so early,

35:08.981 --> 35:09.816
I can go with you,

35:10.024 --> 35:11.651
and get backin time for the parade.

35:11.692 --> 35:13.069
I'll even pay you.

35:13.110 --> 35:13.986
Okay?

35:13.986 --> 35:15.071
No, that's...

35:16.239 --> 35:19.200
I'll drive you.I'll take you free of charge.

35:19.242 --> 35:20.535
Thank you.

35:21.202 --> 35:22.495
No problem.

35:22.495 --> 35:23.746
See you in the morning.

35:23.788 --> 35:24.831
Good night.

35:24.872 --> 35:25.957
'Night.

35:31.170 --> 35:32.547
[♪♪]

35:36.259 --> 35:38.469
>Come on, Ben, think...

35:40.805 --> 35:43.516
[typing]

36:17.633 --> 36:20.720
"10 ThingsYour Driver Won't Tell you:

36:20.720 --> 36:23.472
Rideshare Etiquetteby Ben White."

36:33.190 --> 36:35.484
Okay, my ride is here.

36:35.526 --> 36:36.986
He can't cometo the door?

36:37.028 --> 36:38.154
Not very gentlemanly.

36:38.195 --> 36:39.155
It's not a date.

36:39.197 --> 36:40.364
It could be.

36:40.406 --> 36:42.909
I will be backsoon enough, okay?

36:42.909 --> 36:43.868
If anyone comes in

36:44.118 --> 36:45.328
who remotely looks likea better Santa than Clint,

36:45.369 --> 36:47.038
please lock themin the storeroom.

36:47.079 --> 36:48.206
You're joking, right?

36:48.247 --> 36:49.916
Of course I am.

36:49.916 --> 36:51.167
--Ish.

36:51.208 --> 36:53.044
At least slap onsome lip gloss

36:53.085 --> 36:54.337
before you go.

36:54.378 --> 36:56.213
I will see you later,Caroline.

36:57.089 --> 36:58.215
Bye!

36:59.634 --> 37:01.260
[quietly]It's totally a date.

37:15.399 --> 37:19.445
You know, I read your articleabout Uber drivers.

37:19.487 --> 37:21.989
It's not going to stop mefrom changing the radio station.

37:24.283 --> 37:25.242
Clearly.

37:28.788 --> 37:32.291
You're a reallygood writer.

37:32.333 --> 37:34.752
So you looked me up, huh?

37:34.794 --> 37:36.212
Creepy.

37:38.798 --> 37:40.341
Okay, I looked you up, too.

37:40.383 --> 37:43.219
Your family really changedGreen River for the better.

37:44.887 --> 37:46.013
Yeah.

37:46.055 --> 37:47.765
They were pretty amazing.

37:49.809 --> 37:51.978
I'm sorry you lost themso young.

37:52.019 --> 37:54.313
Thanks.

37:54.313 --> 37:57.566
It's always harderthis time of year.

37:58.442 --> 37:59.485
Wow.

37:59.527 --> 38:02.280
Since when was snowin the forecast?

38:02.321 --> 38:03.781
I thought it was justsupposed to rain.

38:03.823 --> 38:06.117
[radio]: --With an unexpectedly cold storm front,

38:06.158 --> 38:09.495
meteorologists now expect white-out conditions on I-95

38:09.495 --> 38:11.330
from Hartford to Boston

38:11.330 --> 38:13.582
from now until tomorrow morning.

38:13.624 --> 38:15.126
What do you thinkwe should do?

38:15.167 --> 38:16.836
We need to get off the road.

38:21.382 --> 38:23.342
So where are we now?

38:23.384 --> 38:26.846
Uh... Worcester, Mass.

38:26.887 --> 38:28.723
We're halfway betweenBoston and Green River.

38:28.764 --> 38:30.850
They're gonna be closingthe roads on both sides.

38:30.850 --> 38:32.768
But the parade isin less than two days!

38:32.810 --> 38:35.104
I have to get backfor the final preparations.

38:35.146 --> 38:36.772
I don't knowwhat to tell you.

38:36.814 --> 38:39.150
How aboutwe go back in time,

38:39.191 --> 38:40.818
and you tell me,"Hey Grace,

38:40.860 --> 38:41.986
"there's a chanceof snow today,

38:42.069 --> 38:44.030
so you probably shouldn'tcome down to Boston."

38:44.030 --> 38:45.197
Really?

38:45.197 --> 38:46.198
Did you not hear

38:46.240 --> 38:47.658
the "unexpected"part of the forecast?

38:48.868 --> 38:50.161
Look, there's no waywe're gonna make it back now.

38:50.202 --> 38:51.579
We have to figure outwhere to go,

38:51.620 --> 38:53.331
and we can'tstay in the car.

38:53.372 --> 38:55.291
You know what,

38:55.333 --> 38:56.625
one of my best friendsfrom way back

38:56.667 --> 38:57.626
lives near here.

38:57.668 --> 38:59.462
I can see if we crashat her house

38:59.503 --> 39:00.838
till the worstof the storm is over.

39:00.880 --> 39:03.257
I doubt she'll want somestranger in her home.

39:03.299 --> 39:04.925
Any friend of mineis a friend of hers.

39:24.528 --> 39:26.864
Beautiful, right?

39:35.122 --> 39:36.749
Come on.

39:40.002 --> 39:41.212
Hi!

39:42.713 --> 39:43.631
So happy to see you!

39:43.672 --> 39:45.466
How are you guys?So great to see you.

39:45.508 --> 39:47.343
It's been a long time.Good to see you again.

39:47.385 --> 39:49.011
-Hi.-Hi. Ben.

39:49.053 --> 39:49.887
Oh, my goodness,

39:50.054 --> 39:51.347
and who has replacedTucker and Alyx

39:51.389 --> 39:52.389
with these gigantic children?

39:52.431 --> 39:54.016
I'm not a giant.

39:54.058 --> 39:55.559
I'm a mech.

39:55.601 --> 39:57.394
It's a gigantic robot

39:57.436 --> 39:58.604
you climb insideand fight with.

39:58.604 --> 40:00.481
So wait, are youone robot,

40:00.523 --> 40:03.109
or a bunch of robotscombined into a Megabot?

40:03.109 --> 40:05.694
I'm definitely a Megabot!

40:06.445 --> 40:08.489
[whispering]Is he your boyfriend?

40:08.531 --> 40:09.657
No.

40:09.698 --> 40:12.660
No, he's...just a friend.

40:12.701 --> 40:13.702
Everyone, this is Ben.

40:13.744 --> 40:15.621
The storm isreally coming down.

40:15.663 --> 40:17.706
Let's get you guys inside,come on.

40:19.625 --> 40:22.086
Come see our tree.

40:24.713 --> 40:28.092
[Grace]:Oh, what a beautiful tree.

40:28.134 --> 40:30.136
We always wait untilthe kids are on break

40:30.177 --> 40:30.970
to decorate,

40:31.137 --> 40:33.764
so you guys got herejust in time.

40:36.308 --> 40:37.643
Really?

40:37.643 --> 40:38.644
I had nothing to do with that.

40:38.686 --> 40:40.396
[scoffs] Yeah, sure.

40:40.438 --> 40:41.856
I swear.

40:41.897 --> 40:42.857
[Amy]: Do you havesomething against Santa?

40:42.898 --> 40:43.983
[Grace]:Don't go there.

40:44.024 --> 40:45.443
Here you go.

40:55.536 --> 40:56.370
What's wrong?

40:56.412 --> 40:57.538
The roads aren'tgoing to be done

40:57.580 --> 40:58.664
until at least 4:00 a.m.

40:58.664 --> 41:00.666
Well, our guest roomis being renovated,

41:00.708 --> 41:02.960
but we do havea very comfy sectional.

41:03.002 --> 41:04.587
Thank you,

41:04.628 --> 41:05.671
but the parade is in 36 hours,

41:05.713 --> 41:06.964
and I have to get backfor final prep.

41:07.006 --> 41:10.009
Plus I still haveto find somebody to--

41:10.050 --> 41:11.677
Well, you know.

41:11.677 --> 41:13.471
Yeah. I know.

41:13.512 --> 41:15.181
Look, we can't goanywhere tonight,

41:15.222 --> 41:16.682
so let's sleep here,

41:16.682 --> 41:17.766
we'll leave at dawn,get your car,

41:17.892 --> 41:19.685
you'll be back in Green Riverby 9:00 a.m.

41:19.727 --> 41:22.146
Yeah, that could work.

41:22.188 --> 41:23.189
You sure you'll be okay

41:23.355 --> 41:25.816
with all the Christmasspirit here tonight?

41:27.151 --> 41:29.111
I'll make do.

41:29.153 --> 41:30.321
That's the spirit.

41:33.073 --> 41:34.742
[laughing]

41:34.783 --> 41:36.202
Mom, come on,please tell me what it is.

41:36.243 --> 41:37.244
Please!

41:41.540 --> 41:42.416
Can I see that?

41:42.541 --> 41:45.377
I'm really good atguessing presents.

41:45.377 --> 41:46.378
Trust me.

41:48.130 --> 41:49.298
Oh...

41:50.591 --> 41:51.675
Okay, yup.

41:51.717 --> 41:53.052
I know what it is.

41:53.093 --> 41:54.094
What?

41:54.136 --> 41:55.137
It's a turnip.

41:55.179 --> 41:56.055
It is not!

41:56.055 --> 41:56.972
You got a turnip!

41:57.014 --> 41:58.015
[laughter]

41:58.057 --> 41:58.766
No...

41:58.807 --> 41:59.767
[Ben]: Santa brought a turnip.

41:59.808 --> 42:01.060
It's not a turnip...

42:01.101 --> 42:02.228
[giggling]

42:02.269 --> 42:02.937
What's mine?

42:02.978 --> 42:04.313
Yours?Oh, that's easy.

42:05.147 --> 42:05.981
A toaster.

42:06.023 --> 42:09.068
What? No!I don't want a toaster!

42:09.109 --> 42:10.611
I'm sorry, you'regetting a toaster.

42:10.653 --> 42:13.405
This one is to mefrom Jeremy.

42:13.447 --> 42:14.406
Any guesses?

42:14.406 --> 42:15.449
From Jeremy...

42:16.575 --> 42:18.118
No, nothing.

42:18.160 --> 42:21.288
He just thought you mightlike a velour box.

42:21.330 --> 42:22.581
Wow.

42:22.581 --> 42:23.749
You're good.

42:23.749 --> 42:26.085
Okay, French Toast.

42:26.126 --> 42:27.211
[kids cheer] Yes!

42:33.050 --> 42:34.760
"...A wink of his eyeand a twist of his head,

42:34.802 --> 42:38.222
Soon gave me to knowI had nothing to dread--"

42:39.598 --> 42:40.933
That's not the end, Daddy.

42:40.975 --> 42:42.935
The last page is ripped out.

42:42.935 --> 42:45.688
It was an accident.

42:45.729 --> 42:46.689
Nice job, Tucker.

42:46.730 --> 42:49.567
Alyx, he's six.

42:49.608 --> 42:50.442
Give him a break.

42:50.484 --> 42:51.860
Do you rememberthe rest?

42:51.902 --> 42:54.572
Hang on, I'll go online.

43:01.954 --> 43:05.374
"He spoke not a word,but went straight to his work.

43:05.416 --> 43:07.543
"And filled all the stockings,

43:07.585 --> 43:10.045
"then turned with a jerk.

43:10.087 --> 43:12.464
"And laying his fingeraside of his nose,

43:12.464 --> 43:13.882
"and giving a nod,

43:13.924 --> 43:15.968
"up the chimney he rose.

43:15.968 --> 43:18.304
"He sprang to his sleigh,to his team gave a whistle,

43:18.345 --> 43:22.975
"and away they all flewlike the down of a thistle.

43:22.975 --> 43:26.895
"But I heard him exclaim,'ere he drove out of sight..."

43:26.937 --> 43:29.356
[all together]:"Merry Christmas to all,

43:29.398 --> 43:32.067
and to all a good night!"

43:34.862 --> 43:37.239
[♪♪]

43:51.378 --> 43:53.172
You awake?

43:54.340 --> 43:56.216
Yeah.

43:59.386 --> 44:00.471
Goodnight.

44:02.181 --> 44:03.432
Goodnight.

44:35.381 --> 44:36.548
Whatcha doing?

44:37.716 --> 44:39.176
Well...

44:39.218 --> 44:40.677
right now I'm havinga heart attack.

44:40.719 --> 44:42.554
Sorry.

44:42.596 --> 44:44.515
You working on the book?

44:44.556 --> 44:46.308
Yeah, I'm pre-writing.

44:46.350 --> 44:48.310
Oh, what's that mean?

44:48.352 --> 44:50.229
Means I'm trying tofigure out what to write.

44:50.229 --> 44:52.940
I've been pre-writingfor quite some time now.

44:52.981 --> 44:54.400
Hey, what are youdoing up so early?

44:54.400 --> 44:55.401
I had a bad dream.

44:55.401 --> 44:56.693
Let me guess,

44:56.735 --> 44:58.362
it was about not havinga Santa for the parade,

44:58.404 --> 44:59.405
and ruining Christmas?

44:59.405 --> 45:00.406
No.

45:00.406 --> 45:01.490
That would be a nightmare.

45:02.991 --> 45:05.119
Anyway, sinceI'm up so early,

45:05.160 --> 45:06.412
I'm going to seeif Amy has the ingredients

45:06.412 --> 45:07.371
to make eggnog.

45:07.413 --> 45:08.956
You know how to do that?

45:08.997 --> 45:10.582
Yeah, I do it allthe time at the store.

45:10.582 --> 45:13.919
"The World FamousLong Family Recipe."

45:13.919 --> 45:15.421
"World Famous," huh?

45:15.462 --> 45:16.672
Yeah.

45:16.713 --> 45:17.589
So if I do a little...

45:17.589 --> 45:18.715
[clucks tongue]Internet search,

45:18.757 --> 45:19.675
it'll come up?

45:19.717 --> 45:21.552
Mm-hmm.Why don't you try it?

45:22.761 --> 45:25.347
Okay.

45:25.389 --> 45:27.099
Let's see.

45:27.099 --> 45:29.184
"Long Family egg--"

45:30.728 --> 45:31.812
Oh.

45:31.854 --> 45:32.771
Yeah, it auto-completed"to eggnog", didn't it?

45:32.813 --> 45:33.939
Yes.

45:33.981 --> 45:35.149
Yes, it did.

45:36.775 --> 45:38.444
Impressive.

45:38.444 --> 45:39.528
Okay, but wait,

45:39.570 --> 45:41.488
who's the lumberjack?

45:41.530 --> 45:42.489
Oh.

45:42.531 --> 45:43.949
That's my ex. Mark.

45:43.991 --> 45:46.952
He moved to Oregonabout a year ago.

45:46.994 --> 45:48.454
No one since?

45:48.454 --> 45:49.496
No.

45:49.538 --> 45:50.748
I've just been focusing on work.

45:50.789 --> 45:51.999
What about you?

45:52.040 --> 45:55.669
Lots of potentialin Boston, I imagine.

45:55.711 --> 45:57.629
Aspiring novelists/slash/Uber drivers

45:57.671 --> 45:59.047
aren't exactly making the list

45:59.089 --> 46:01.592
of "Boston's Most EligibleBachelors."

46:01.633 --> 46:02.634
Yeah, but I mean,

46:02.968 --> 46:05.053
you at least broke awayfrom your family's expectations,

46:05.095 --> 46:06.805
and went and chasedyour dream.

46:06.805 --> 46:08.682
I'd imaginea lot of women love that.

46:08.724 --> 46:10.225
So you did have other dreams.

46:10.267 --> 46:11.977
Oh, we weren't talkingabout me.

46:12.019 --> 46:14.938
Okay, I think I haveall the ingredients I need.

46:14.980 --> 46:18.108
Milk, cream, eggs, and sugar.

46:18.150 --> 46:19.777
Okay, what spicesdo you need?

46:19.818 --> 46:22.112
I am not at liberty to say.

46:23.071 --> 46:25.991
Okay, so we start this

46:25.991 --> 46:29.453
by pouring inthe milk and cream.

46:29.495 --> 46:30.287
So, what other dreams

46:30.496 --> 46:31.455
did you havein your life, Grace?

46:36.001 --> 46:37.002
It doesn't matter.

46:37.002 --> 46:38.795
Oh, I thinkit does.

46:38.837 --> 46:39.838
I think it does.

46:39.838 --> 46:42.758
You've been judging meabout it non-stop.

46:42.800 --> 46:44.218
Come on,cone of silence.

46:44.259 --> 46:45.636
I know you lovethe store.

46:45.677 --> 46:46.678
I do love it.

46:46.929 --> 46:47.888
Well, what did you dreamabout doing with your life

46:48.180 --> 46:50.307
before you took it overfor your parents?

46:51.975 --> 46:54.520
I was goingto art school, okay?

46:54.561 --> 46:58.649
But then my parents diedright after high school,

46:58.690 --> 46:59.691
and, uh...

46:59.733 --> 47:01.360
then I wound upstaying home.

47:02.486 --> 47:03.403
And that's okay.

47:03.445 --> 47:05.364
I still get to paint,

47:05.364 --> 47:08.033
I just sell my workin the back of the store.

47:08.033 --> 47:10.285
It's okay.

47:12.579 --> 47:15.874
Okay, well...

47:15.916 --> 47:17.709
Next up...

47:17.751 --> 47:19.378
it's the eggsand the sugar.

47:19.378 --> 47:21.964
Shoo! Go away.

47:22.005 --> 47:23.465
Right.

47:23.507 --> 47:25.300
Like that...

47:25.342 --> 47:27.427
Pour a little bit of that in...

47:28.262 --> 47:29.847
One of these...[cracking egg]

47:31.014 --> 47:32.933
There we go.

47:32.975 --> 47:34.685
All right.

47:34.726 --> 47:35.811
Then you stir the pot,

47:35.853 --> 47:37.855
which you obviouslyenjoy doing.

47:40.899 --> 47:42.901
Now...

47:42.943 --> 47:44.611
time for the secret spices.

47:44.653 --> 47:45.404
Close your eyes.

47:45.404 --> 47:47.948
This is really unnecessary,

47:47.990 --> 47:49.157
you know that, right?

47:49.199 --> 47:50.284
I saw you peeking.

47:51.910 --> 47:53.579
Okay.

47:53.579 --> 47:54.788
Little of that.

47:56.540 --> 47:57.833
Little of this...

48:01.545 --> 48:02.212
All right,

48:02.254 --> 48:03.630
you want the first taste?

48:03.672 --> 48:06.592
Yeah, I'm not really muchof a "nog" connoisseur.

48:06.633 --> 48:07.634
Come on.

48:07.676 --> 48:09.553
It's famous, remember?

48:09.595 --> 48:12.306
Trust me,it's amazing.

48:13.515 --> 48:15.517
All right.

48:17.060 --> 48:18.020
Wow.

48:18.061 --> 48:19.938
See?

48:19.938 --> 48:21.732
I told you you could trust me.

48:22.608 --> 48:24.526
-More?-Sure.

48:24.568 --> 48:25.944
-Oh!-Really?

48:25.944 --> 48:27.613
Sorry. [laughs]

48:28.655 --> 48:30.490
It's all over...

48:31.992 --> 48:34.703
[all cheering]Eggnog! Eggnog! Eggnog!

48:34.745 --> 48:35.787
[Amy]: It smellsso good in here!

48:35.787 --> 48:36.788
Can we have some?

48:36.788 --> 48:37.873
Yeah!Absolutely.

48:38.165 --> 48:39.625
-Did you just make it fresh?-You guys want some eggnog?

48:39.625 --> 48:41.126
Smells amazing.

48:41.126 --> 48:42.377
Tell me what you think.

48:43.462 --> 48:44.630
It looks so good.

48:44.630 --> 48:45.714
You guys want some?

48:45.756 --> 48:48.467
Yes.Love some, yeah.

48:48.508 --> 48:49.801
[ringing bells]

48:49.843 --> 48:51.136
Well done.

48:51.178 --> 48:53.055
Sounding good, sounding good...

48:53.096 --> 48:54.473
Oh, beautiful, beautiful.

48:54.514 --> 48:55.515
[cowbell clanking]

48:55.557 --> 48:56.975
Oh, no, no,okay, that's a bad bell.

48:57.017 --> 48:58.018
We'll swap that out,

48:58.060 --> 49:00.020
don't you worry.

49:00.062 --> 49:01.146
[bells tinkling]And ringing, and ringing, and--

49:01.146 --> 49:02.814
Okay, that's me

49:02.814 --> 49:04.024
Take a break, guys.

49:04.066 --> 49:05.901
Where are you?

49:05.943 --> 49:07.653
We'll be leavingin a few minutes.

49:07.653 --> 49:09.154
How's Worcester?

49:09.196 --> 49:10.656
I've been tryingto reach Grace.

49:10.697 --> 49:12.199
Is that her?

49:12.240 --> 49:13.825
Oh, no.No, no, no, no, no. Stall her.

49:13.825 --> 49:15.327
She's on an errand.

49:15.369 --> 49:16.578
She'll be back in a bit.

49:16.620 --> 49:17.663
Ah.

49:17.704 --> 49:19.831
But everything'sokay, right?

49:19.873 --> 49:22.167
It's Christmas in Green River.

49:22.209 --> 49:23.085
[chuckles]

49:23.126 --> 49:24.795
You didn't answer my question.

49:24.836 --> 49:26.713
I'll tell her to call you.

49:27.547 --> 49:28.840
Okay, bye.

49:29.841 --> 49:30.842
Is she gone?

49:30.842 --> 49:32.094
For now.

49:32.135 --> 49:33.011
When are you coming back?

49:33.011 --> 49:34.262
Soon.

49:34.304 --> 49:35.931
Why, is there actuallyanother problem?

49:35.972 --> 49:37.391
You know, besides the fact

49:37.432 --> 49:38.475
that we don't have a Santa,

49:38.684 --> 49:40.018
we might lose the "Good Day, USA" spot,

49:40.060 --> 49:41.353
and most likelypermanently damage

49:41.395 --> 49:43.063
the entire town's income stream?

49:43.105 --> 49:44.731
No, everything's fine.

49:44.773 --> 49:46.108
[gasps] Wait!No, it isn't!

49:46.149 --> 49:47.234
What?

49:47.275 --> 49:49.695
You didn't RSVP tomy ugly sweater party tonight.

49:49.695 --> 49:50.987
[sighs]

49:51.029 --> 49:52.322
Goodbye, Caroline.

49:52.364 --> 49:54.741
But you saidwe could go see Santa

49:54.783 --> 49:55.867
at the mall this morning.

49:55.867 --> 49:56.952
[tsks] Aw, buddy.

49:56.994 --> 49:58.829
You have a fever.

49:58.870 --> 50:00.539
We can't do it,I'm sorry.

50:00.580 --> 50:02.082
But you promised.

50:02.124 --> 50:03.125
How about we sit down

50:03.166 --> 50:05.335
and write Santaa letter instead?

50:05.377 --> 50:08.088
But Christmas Eveis tomorrow night.

50:08.130 --> 50:10.132
He'll never get it in time.

50:10.173 --> 50:11.133
Email, then.

50:11.174 --> 50:13.427
Last year, you saidSanta didn't do email!

50:13.468 --> 50:15.887
If we don't get to seeSanta in person,

50:15.887 --> 50:17.097
he won't knowwhat we want.

50:17.139 --> 50:18.056
He won't come.

50:18.056 --> 50:19.266
He won't come?

50:19.307 --> 50:20.892
Of course,he will, buddy.

50:20.934 --> 50:23.145
No, he won't!

50:23.186 --> 50:24.896
[crying]I want Santa!

50:24.896 --> 50:26.481
[mom]: Oh, sweetie.

50:30.360 --> 50:32.821
[doorbell rings]

50:35.615 --> 50:37.159
Ho-ho-ho!

50:37.200 --> 50:40.287
Merry Christmas,Sheridan family!

50:40.328 --> 50:42.372
[together]: Santa!

50:45.083 --> 50:46.293
It's Santa!You came!

50:46.334 --> 50:47.335
You actually came!

50:47.377 --> 50:49.004
Yes, I did...

50:49.045 --> 50:50.922
I have a surprise for you.

50:50.922 --> 50:52.716
-Thank you!-[whispers]: Thank you.

50:53.675 --> 50:54.426
Come on over.

50:54.426 --> 50:57.679
Tucker, come siton my lap.

50:57.721 --> 50:59.097
You really know my name?

50:59.139 --> 51:01.308
Of course, I know your name.

51:01.349 --> 51:03.894
I also know you've beena very good boy.

51:03.935 --> 51:06.772
So, what would you likefor Christmas?

51:06.772 --> 51:07.939
Wait, let me guess,

51:07.939 --> 51:09.858
something to do with robots?

51:09.900 --> 51:11.276
Yes, please.

51:11.318 --> 51:12.277
And Legos,

51:12.277 --> 51:13.236
and a puppy,

51:13.278 --> 51:15.113
and a new baby brother!

51:15.113 --> 51:16.406
Well...

51:16.448 --> 51:17.407
Legos and robots I can do,

51:17.491 --> 51:19.367
but a new brother...[chuckles awkwardly]

51:19.409 --> 51:20.869
I'll have to passthat message on

51:20.911 --> 51:21.953
to the right department.

51:21.953 --> 51:23.079
Thank you, Santa.

51:23.121 --> 51:24.915
You're welcome, Tucker.

51:27.083 --> 51:30.003
Alyx, I've seen how kindand generous you are.

51:30.045 --> 51:32.047
You're a wonderful big sister.

51:32.088 --> 51:33.215
She's the best.

51:33.256 --> 51:35.967
So, what would you likefor Christmas?

51:36.009 --> 51:37.969
Nothing with princesses on it.

51:38.011 --> 51:39.971
No princesses, got it.

51:39.971 --> 51:41.223
I like your style.

51:41.264 --> 51:42.974
So, what wouldyou like instead?

51:43.016 --> 51:44.059
Ooh...

51:44.101 --> 51:45.101
a microscope, please.

51:45.143 --> 51:47.229
And a rock tumbler, please.

51:47.270 --> 51:48.897
Oh...

51:48.939 --> 51:50.649
[quietly]And no more brothers.

51:50.690 --> 51:52.609
Please.

51:52.651 --> 51:54.736
Okay. [chuckling]Santa will do his best.

51:54.778 --> 51:56.029
Thanks, Santa.

51:56.071 --> 51:58.073
Well, kids,

51:58.114 --> 51:59.574
I bet Santa has to get going.

51:59.616 --> 52:01.117
I'm sure he's gotother kids with fevers

52:01.159 --> 52:02.077
to visit today.

52:02.119 --> 52:03.829
Yes, I'll be backtomorrow night,

52:03.870 --> 52:06.123
so make sure you get to bednice and early.

52:06.164 --> 52:07.207
[kids together]:We will!

52:07.249 --> 52:09.251
I love you, Santa.

52:09.292 --> 52:10.919
Santa loves you, too.

52:14.089 --> 52:15.966
Wait, Santa, you can't leave.

52:16.007 --> 52:17.843
You have to meet Mr. Ben.

52:17.843 --> 52:20.053
He's so cool.

52:20.095 --> 52:21.596
Uh, well, you know,

52:21.638 --> 52:23.265
I think Mr. Ben is actuallydown on the main road

52:23.306 --> 52:25.350
looking at the conditions.

52:25.350 --> 52:26.893
But I'm sure he's made itonto the "nice" list.

52:26.935 --> 52:28.395
Right, Santa?

52:28.436 --> 52:29.980
He's trying.

52:31.064 --> 52:32.858
Okay, kids, well,have a great Christmas!

52:32.899 --> 52:34.860
Ho-ho-ho!

52:34.901 --> 52:35.861
Bye, Santa!

52:35.861 --> 52:36.862
Merry Christmas!

52:36.903 --> 52:38.363
Bye, Santa!

52:38.363 --> 52:41.032
Best Christmas ever.

52:41.032 --> 52:42.993
[laughs] Come here.

52:48.874 --> 52:49.875
Ben...

52:49.875 --> 52:51.042
That was amazing.

52:51.042 --> 52:52.961
Thank you for that.

52:54.462 --> 52:55.714
How did you knowthe suit was in the car?

52:56.548 --> 52:58.633
I, uh, I found it therethis morning.

52:58.675 --> 53:00.719
I was just going to giveit back to my dad, but...

53:00.719 --> 53:03.013
I guess there was a reasonit was still there.

53:04.389 --> 53:06.057
I know that was hard for you.

53:07.809 --> 53:09.394
It wasn't that hard,

53:09.436 --> 53:10.770
but don't tell my dad.

53:10.812 --> 53:12.147
I don't want themto get their hopes up.

53:13.231 --> 53:15.233
But... you kind ofgot mine up again.

53:15.233 --> 53:17.027
I am sorry, Grace,

53:17.068 --> 53:18.570
but I have to get backto Boston.

53:18.570 --> 53:19.738
It's my busiest week.

53:19.738 --> 53:21.114
The rent's not goingto pay itself.

53:21.156 --> 53:22.324
Know what, fine, fine,

53:22.449 --> 53:24.201
let's just hurry back up thereand get my car, okay?

53:24.242 --> 53:26.578
I can't believe I leftthis close to the parade.

53:26.620 --> 53:29.706
You thought you hadanother shot at convincing me.

53:31.374 --> 53:33.084
Maybe I just likehanging out with you.

53:33.084 --> 53:35.086
Did you ever thinkabout that?

53:36.463 --> 53:38.173
[chuckles]

53:38.215 --> 53:41.551
I think about it a lot,actually.

53:45.472 --> 53:47.766
[shivering]

53:47.807 --> 53:49.226
Well, we got the sidewalkand driveway clear.

53:49.267 --> 53:51.686
Oh, great, so we canget back up to Boston.

53:51.728 --> 53:54.648
The only open roadsare the ones going south.

53:54.689 --> 53:55.732
But we have to get my car

53:55.774 --> 53:56.608
and get back downfor the parade.

53:56.650 --> 53:59.444
It's in less than24 hours.

53:59.444 --> 54:01.237
You want me to take youto Green River, don't you?

54:02.489 --> 54:03.698
Could you?

54:03.740 --> 54:06.117
Please?

54:06.159 --> 54:07.118
Bye, guys!

54:07.118 --> 54:08.411
Bye, everyone!

54:08.453 --> 54:09.329
Merry Christmas!

54:09.371 --> 54:10.330
Bye, Merry Christmas!

54:10.372 --> 54:11.581
Drive safe!

54:11.623 --> 54:13.333
Bye, Merry Christmas!

54:13.375 --> 54:15.251
Merry Christmas!Happy New Year!

54:17.128 --> 54:18.296
They are such a great family.

54:18.296 --> 54:21.132
I miss having that.

54:21.132 --> 54:23.301
You know,it's funny...

54:23.301 --> 54:24.302
What?

54:24.302 --> 54:25.387
I always thought

54:25.470 --> 54:27.180
if I was tryingto get away from my legacy,

54:27.222 --> 54:28.640
I'd have to go as far awayas I could,

54:28.640 --> 54:31.351
but after beingat Amy's house...

54:31.393 --> 54:35.981
I kind of forgothow Christmas felt.

54:37.232 --> 54:38.275
Yeah.

54:38.316 --> 54:40.568
I mean, I kind of forgothow Christmas felt, too.

54:40.610 --> 54:42.320
You owna Christmas store.

54:42.320 --> 54:43.321
You told me yourself

54:43.446 --> 54:46.157
you feel the Christmas spiritevery day.

54:46.157 --> 54:48.702
Well, yeah, but...

54:49.744 --> 54:50.787
I don't know,I guess it'd be like,

54:50.996 --> 54:52.998
if you celebrated your birthdayevery day.

54:52.998 --> 54:54.833
After a while, it just...

54:54.874 --> 54:57.502
it wouldn't feel specialanymore, right?

54:57.544 --> 55:00.130
And I guess somewherealong the way,

55:00.171 --> 55:03.508
Christmas became a job.

55:03.550 --> 55:07.053
I just didn't realize ituntil now.

55:08.513 --> 55:09.723
So quit.

55:11.182 --> 55:12.684
I can't.

55:12.726 --> 55:15.020
The whole town depends onChristmas,

55:15.061 --> 55:16.855
especially the parade.

55:16.855 --> 55:20.358
I knew that that would bemy responsibility

55:20.400 --> 55:21.526
when I took overthe store.

55:21.526 --> 55:23.695
But it's okay.

55:23.695 --> 55:28.033
I'm happy knowing that what I domakes other people happy.

55:29.200 --> 55:30.785
What about you?

55:30.827 --> 55:31.745
Hmm?

55:31.786 --> 55:33.997
Don't you deserveto be happy, too?

55:40.628 --> 55:41.713
[turns onChristmas radio station]

55:41.713 --> 55:44.799
♪ Deck the hallswith boughs of holly ♪

55:44.841 --> 55:48.053
♪ Fa-la-la la-lala-la-la-la ♪

55:48.094 --> 55:49.846
No light jazz?

55:49.888 --> 55:51.514
No.

55:51.556 --> 55:53.183
This is perfect.

55:53.224 --> 55:56.311
♪ 'Tis the seasonto be jolly ♪

55:56.353 --> 55:59.647
♪ Fa-la-la la-lala-la-la-la ♪

55:59.689 --> 56:01.858
[♪♪]

56:02.609 --> 56:04.986
It is so magical hereafter a snowstorm, isn't it?

56:05.028 --> 56:07.238
Like a painting?

56:07.238 --> 56:09.240
Smooth.

56:09.240 --> 56:10.367
Be right back.

56:10.408 --> 56:11.826
Okay.

56:14.245 --> 56:15.246
Oh, excuse me.

56:15.288 --> 56:16.915
Is that Ben?

56:16.956 --> 56:17.707
Yes, but--

56:17.791 --> 56:18.833
Oh, thank goodness, he's here!

56:19.167 --> 56:20.251
I was five minutes awayfrom letting the network know

56:20.251 --> 56:21.336
that we didn't have a Santa.

56:21.378 --> 56:22.253
That would've been bad.

56:22.253 --> 56:23.254
Like, so bad.

56:23.254 --> 56:24.339
I probably would've got fired.

56:24.380 --> 56:26.216
And thenshowcasing Clint

56:26.257 --> 56:26.925
on national television?

56:27.133 --> 56:29.552
[wincing]Ooh, total nightmare

56:29.594 --> 56:31.012
for you and the town.

56:31.054 --> 56:31.846
Well, anyway,

56:32.013 --> 56:33.014
all of that'sbehind us now, so--

56:33.056 --> 56:34.224
[cell phone ringing]

56:34.265 --> 56:35.642
There they are.Okay. Yeah.

56:35.683 --> 56:37.310
Yes. Ben is here.

56:37.352 --> 56:39.562
Karen, are youhearing me?

56:39.604 --> 56:40.438
He's perfect...

56:40.480 --> 56:42.232
Chestnuts--

56:42.273 --> 56:43.691
Grace!

56:43.733 --> 56:45.068
Grace, wherehave you been?

56:45.110 --> 56:46.361
We have a huge issue.

56:46.402 --> 56:47.612
What?What's wrong?

56:47.612 --> 56:50.240
My baritone refuses to singin our Christmas Quartet

56:50.281 --> 56:51.282
if he has to wear the hat.

56:51.282 --> 56:53.368
Oh, I see.

56:53.409 --> 56:55.370
What's so bad about a hat?

56:57.580 --> 56:59.457
Uh, well, Stan,

56:59.499 --> 57:01.292
as festive as your hats areevery year...

57:01.334 --> 57:02.502
Thank you.

57:02.544 --> 57:03.711
...I can't force someoneto wear a costume

57:03.753 --> 57:05.422
if they don't really want to.

57:06.840 --> 57:08.758
That was really meantfor me though, right?

57:10.343 --> 57:11.761
[Stan sighs]

57:11.803 --> 57:14.431
Yes, but you weresupposed to know

57:14.472 --> 57:15.431
I was talkingabout you,

57:15.473 --> 57:17.142
without actuallyacknowledging it.

57:17.183 --> 57:19.352
That's whyit's called subtext.

57:19.394 --> 57:21.855
I don't do subtext.

57:21.896 --> 57:22.814
Really?

57:22.856 --> 57:24.899
You just...tell it like it is?

57:24.941 --> 57:26.484
You don't keepanything inside?

57:26.526 --> 57:27.443
That's right.

57:27.485 --> 57:29.821
So, what are you thinkingright now?

57:30.697 --> 57:31.823
[singing]♪ Dashing through the snow

57:31.865 --> 57:34.868
♪ In a one-horse open sleigh

57:34.909 --> 57:37.120
♪ Over the hills we go

57:37.162 --> 57:38.413
♪ Laughing all the way

57:38.454 --> 57:39.581
♪ Ha-ha-ha!

57:39.622 --> 57:41.082
Well, you are certainly

57:41.124 --> 57:42.584
brimming withChristmas spirit today,

57:42.625 --> 57:43.585
aren't you?

57:43.626 --> 57:45.003
I'm just singing.

57:45.044 --> 57:46.337
Don't read into it.

57:46.337 --> 57:48.298
I'm not.

57:57.348 --> 57:59.058
[sighs]What's this?

57:59.100 --> 58:00.351
Oh, this is great.

58:00.393 --> 58:01.811
Each of the businesseson Main Street

58:01.853 --> 58:03.688
decorates a tree for the float.

58:03.688 --> 58:06.316
So, this one's for the store.

58:06.357 --> 58:07.400
Caroline just finished it.

58:10.028 --> 58:11.362
Oh...

58:11.362 --> 58:12.363
It's for your dad's school.

58:12.405 --> 58:14.032
Oh...

58:14.073 --> 58:15.492
they must not havegotten around to it.

58:16.659 --> 58:18.411
I get a discountat your store, right?

58:18.453 --> 58:20.496
Only for friends and family.

58:20.538 --> 58:22.081
Come on.

58:25.543 --> 58:27.003
Oh, uh...

58:27.045 --> 58:28.796
[chuckling]

58:30.256 --> 58:31.758
What? Closed?

58:31.799 --> 58:34.385
Why are we closed?

58:34.385 --> 58:35.553
What's going on?

58:35.553 --> 58:36.512
Why are we closed?

58:36.554 --> 58:38.223
You don't wantto go in here.

58:38.264 --> 58:39.724
Why not?

58:39.724 --> 58:42.060
Tom is giving Clinta Santa lesson.

58:42.060 --> 58:44.229
Well, that's a good thing,isn't it?

58:44.270 --> 58:45.230
Well...

58:45.230 --> 58:46.231
no--

58:46.231 --> 58:47.190
Ah!

58:47.232 --> 58:48.483
I'm just gonna go inside.

